article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- — Matt Allocco scored 25 points and made five 3-pointers to help Princeton defeat Dartmouth 76-58 on Monday. Allocco also had five assists for the Tigers (14-1, 2-0 Ivy League). Caden Pierce scored 18 points while shooting 6 for 9 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 5 of 8 from the free throw line, and added 10 rebounds. Xaivian Lee shot 4 for 8 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 7 of 7 from the free throw line to finish with 16 points. Brandon Mitchell-Day led the way for the Big Green (4-11, 0-2) with 15 points. Izaiah Robinson added 13 points and two blocks for Dartmouth. Dusan Neskovic also put up 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
